summary: I am a multicultural and multilingual Magna Cum Laude graduate with degrees in International Relations, General Psychology, and Management. Experience with topics such as cross-cultural communication, access to information & education, and environmental issues supplements my technical expertise in these fields. I am adaptable, open-minded, and culturally sensitive. My drive for personal and professional growth has led to work experience on 3 continents in various fields, including customer service, teaching, and administrative assistance.

volunteer_experiences:
[{'date': {'start': {'month': 9, 'day': None, 'year': 2019}, 'end': {'month': 12, 'day': None, 'year': 2019}}, 'role': 'Family Partner', 'company': {'id': None, 'name': 'Welcome Neighbor STL', 'logo': 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/C4D0BAQGWCC4Q0KRWsQ/company-logo_400_400/0/1558456635937?e=1700697600&v=beta&t=QI2svLX5ovJXUkEWI0X0EM-Y0F8omYs1FthTLV4geio', 'url': 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/welcome-neighbor-stl/'}, 'cause': 'CIVIL_RIGHTS', 'description': 'I spent 4 months being a ‘family partner’ to a Syrian refugee family that recently moved to St. Louis. The role of a family partner is to provide holistic support for new immigrant families. 

- tutored 3 ESL primary school boys in school subjects as needed, such as math, social studies, and science
- provided one-on-one support for recent immigrant parents who were studying for the U.S. Citizenship Test
- volunteered at Neighbourhood Supper Clubs by serving guests and supported refugee women during post-dinner Q&A
- accompanied the family to various activities (e.g. grocery shopping or sporting events) to help them navigate cultural differences or unfamiliarities
- made weekly visits to the family to help with tasks such as reading and understanding government mail, paying bills, calling phone/cable companies, etc. that are more difficult with a language barrier.
'}]
